== Answers to Set Theory Exercise 1 ==
1 : (a) Yes; alphanumeric characters are A…Z, a…z and 0…9 : (b) No; 'tall' is not well-defined : (c) Yes; the set is {12.5} : (d) Yes; the empty set : (e) No; 'good' is not well-defined
2 : (a) T : (b) F : (c) T : (d) F; ''A'' is a ''[[../#Subsets|subset]]'' of U (which we meet in the next section) : (e) F; {even numbers} means the set of ''all'' the even numbers, not just those between 2 and 10
3 : (a) {4, 33, &radic;9} : (b) {4, -5, 33, &radic;9} : (c) {4, 2/3, -2.5, -5, 33, &radic;9} : (d) {&radic;2, π}
4 : (a) F : (b) T : (c) F : (d) T
5 Examples might include: : (a) {London, Paris, Rome, …} : (b) {1, 3, 5, 7, …}, but not –3 or –1 : (c) {5, -5} : (d) {3, 27, 243, …}
