{{BookCat}}

{{:Radiation_Oncology:TOC}}
<big>'''Hemangioendothelioma'''</big>
*Rare tumor *Intermediate-grade malignant tumors, clinically behaving between benign hemangioma and malignant angiosarcoma. Some have rather benign course while others show much more malignant progression *Typically occur in adults with roughly equal sex distribution *Most common location is soft tissues, but have been described essentially anywhere in the body *Symptoms depend upon location of the primary tumor *Most common histologic type is epithelioid hmangioendothelioma (EHE) *For isolated tumors, curative resection with negative margin should be performed *Role of adjuvant RT is unclear, but is often considered *Most common metastatic sites are lungs, liver, lymph nodes and bone *Effectiveness of chemotherapy is unclear *Most studies are small single institution series

